      "body" : "@StephaneEybert (or anyone else) The single quotes mean that something is a literal character to be expected in the string, and is not to be considered part of the pattern. For instance: if your date comes in as &quot;2015-08-dd30&quot; for some reason, you would specify &quot;yyyy-MM-&#39;dd&#39;dd&quot;, indicating that the first dd is a literal part expected in the string, and the second dd (outside of the apostrophes) is the actual day that needs to be parsed. So in your earlier case it would have worked if instead of the actual timezone you would have put &quot;ZZ&quot; at the end of your incoming datetime-string."
